import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    country_counts = data.groupby('country').size().sort_values(ascending=False)
    if len(country_counts) > 20:
        country_counts = country_counts[:20]
    ax = country_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    ax.yaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(integer=True))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['state'] = data['state'].astype('category')
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = state_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports by state?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    for i, v in enumerate(state_counts):
        ax.text(i, v + 10, str(v), ha='center')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['longitude'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Airports')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport locations by longitude?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name'] = data['name'].astype(str)
    airport_names = ' '.join(data['name'].tolist())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.imshow(WordCloud(width=800, height=800, background_color='white').generate(airport_names))
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
